LinuxCNC EtherCAT Configuration

This repository contains configuration files for integrating LinuxCNC with EtherCAT devices.  
The setup includes three servo drives and one I/O bus, configured for motion control applications.

---

System Overview

| Device Type	| Model				| EtherCAT Slave Index 	| Description |
|---------------|-------------------|-----------------------|--------------|
| Servo Drive	| Inovance SV630N	| Slave 0				| Axis 1 |
| Servo Drive	| Inovance SV630N	| Slave 1 				| Axis 2 |
| Servo Drive	| Luwei X5S			| Slave 2 				| Axis 3 |
| I/O Bus		| PINVICT			| Slave 3 				| Digital and Analog I/O |

---

Features

- Compatible with LinuxCNC + EtherCAT HAL integration  
- Basic mapped PDO entries for each slave  
- Example HAL and XML configuration files  
- Predefined mappings for:
  - Position, velocity, and torque loops
  - Enable, alarm reset, and status bits
  - Digital and analog inputs/outputs

---

Requirements

- **LinuxCNC** (tested with version 2.9+)
- **EtherCAT master** (IgH EtherCAT master)
- **SOEM drivers** for supported servo drives
- **Real-time kernel** (e.g., PREEMPT_RT)


